properties.Name: FastqIlluminaSequenceIdentifierPreVersion14
properties.Description:
Illumina sequence identifiers prior to version 1.4

Sequences from the Illumina software use a systematic identifier:

EX:
@HWUSI-EAS100R:6:73:941:1973#0/1

HWUSI-EAS100R   the unique instrument name
6              flowcell lane
73            tile number within the flowcell lane
941          'x'-coordinate of the cluster within the tile
1973        'y'-coordinate of the cluster within the tile
#0            index number for a multiplexed sample (0 for no indexing)
/1             the member of a pair, /1 or /2 (paired-end or mate-pair reads only)

Columns.Name: GeneSequencingFileFormatId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a gene sequencing file format.

Columns.Name: XCoordinateOfTheClusterWithinTheTile
Columns.Description: The 'x'-coordinate of the cluster within the tile.

Columns.Name: YCoordinateOfTheClusterWithinTheTile
Columns.Description: The 'y'-coordinate of the cluster within the tile.

Columns.Name: IndexNumberForAMultiplexedSample
Columns.Description: The index number for a multiplexed sample (0 for no indexing).

Columns.Name: MemberOfAPair
Columns.Description: The member of a pair, /1 or /2 (paired-end or mate-pair reads only).
